reviewText: Dissapointing.  This is a biography of Rap Remlinger but doesn't show any skits at all which I was hoping for.
Like his work but I thought that the presentation was weak. I liked the CDs better.

I being from Hawaii loved Rap Replinger's sense of humor. Though, he's been gone for a while, I find that his timing and comedic sense is timely. I have a sister that still lives in Hawaii and she tells me that his Pidgin is "outdated" but I love what he's done and for me, I think that his language skills is timeless.
it was not what I thought it would be,if I could send it back I would,
For locals, it's a classic that you just have to own. If you're one mainlander, this will give you an idea of how we laugh about each other, together, with aloha.
